{"word":"ἀγρέω","slug":"ἀγρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγρέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> form of <a href='S:ἀγρεύω'><el>ἀγρεύω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to capture, seize</i>, <b><a href='S:Sappho Lyrica'>Sapph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:imperative mood'>imperat.</a> <el>ἄγρει,  ἄγε</el>, <i>come, come on</i> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>ἀγρεῖτε</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}